===Coaching history===
{{Further|List of Belgium national football team managers}}
Since 1904, the RBFA, 26 permanent managers and two caretaker managers have officially been in charge of the national team;{{efn|The interim managers were [[Louis Nicolay]] and [[Franky Vercauteren]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Geschiedenis van de Rode Duivels |trans-title=History of the Red Devils |language=nl |url=http://cms1.proximedia.com/site/33301/page.asp?docid=37813&langue=NL |access-date=9 May 2014 |publisher=Bel 2 Mundial |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160721104224/http://cms1.proximedia.com/site/33301/page.asp?docid=37813&langue=NL |archive-date=21 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.gva.be/cnt/aid828724/vercauteren-interim-bondscoach-rode-duivels |title=Vercauteren interim-bondscoach Rode Duivels |trans-title=Vercauteren caretaker manager Red Devils |language=nl |newspaper=[[Gazet Van Antwerpen]] |first=W. |last=Verhaert |date=5 May 2009 |access-date=19 July 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160721104337/http://www.gva.be/cnt/aid828724/vercauteren-interim-bondscoach-rode-duivels |archive-date=21 July 2016}}</ref>}}<ref name="manrsssf"/><ref name="HN060612"/> this includes one national footballer selector.<ref name="manrsssf">{{cite web |url=https://www.rsssf.org/miscellaneous/belg-coach.html |title=Belgium National Team Coaches |first=Hassanin |last=Mubarak |date=7 August 2003 |access-date=14 September 2013 |website=[[RSSSF]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160629193505/http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/belg-coach.html |archive-date=29 June 2016}}</ref> {{As of|2025|01}}, a crew of over 30 RBFA employees guides the player group, including French head coach [[Rudi Garcia]], and assistant coaches [[Andreas Hinkel]] and Luke Benstead.<ref name="staff"/> Under [[Marc Wilmots]], Belgium reached the top FIFA ranking spot in 2015, which earned him the title of Best Coach of the Year at the 2015 [[Globe Soccer Awards]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Globe-soccer-awards-le-triple-pour-le-barca-le-double-pour-new-york-city/619774 |title=Globe Soccer Awards : le triplé pour le Barça, le doublé pour New York City |trans-title=Globe Soccer Awards: the triple for Barça, the double for New York City |newspaper=[[L'Équipe]] |language=fr |date=27 December 2015 |access-date=27 December 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160701154055/http://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Globe-soccer-awards-le-triple-pour-le-barca-le-double-pour-new-york-city/619774 |archive-date=1 July 2016}}</ref> Guy Thys received [[World Soccer (magazine)|''World Soccer'' magazine]]'s Manager of the Year in 1986 after results at the World Cup and Euros.<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.worldsoccer.com/features/world-soccer-awards-previous-winners-2-338433 |title=World Soccer Awards – previous winners |first=Jamie |last=Rainbow |journal=[[World Soccer (magazine)|World Soccer]] |date=14 December 2012 |access-date=29 April 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160629194202/http://www.worldsoccer.com/features/world-soccer-awards-previous-winners-2-338433 |archive-date=29 June 2016}}</ref> Under Spanish coach [[Roberto Martínez]], the team reached a best-ever third place finish at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]].

Rather than developing innovative team formations or styles of play, Belgium's managers applied conventional tactics. At the three World Cups in the 1930s, the Red Devils were aligned in a contemporary [[Formation (association football)|2–3–5 "pyramid"]].<ref name="rsssf30">{{cite web |url=https://www.rsssf.org/tables/30full.html |title=World Cup 1930 finals |access-date=17 August 2015 |website=[[RSSSF]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160629194350/http://www.rsssf.com/tables/30full.html |archive-date=29 June 2016}}</ref><ref name="rsssf34"/><ref name="rsssf38">{{cite web |url=https://www.rsssf.org/tables/38full.html |title=World Cup 1938 finals |access-date=17 August 2015 |website=[[RSSSF]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160629194457/http://www.rsssf.com/tables/38full.html |archive-date=29 June 2016}}</ref> In 1954, [[Doug Livingstone]]'s squad played in a [[Formation (association football)|3–2–5 "WM" arrangement]] during World Cup matches.<ref name="rsssf54">{{cite web |url=https://www.rsssf.org/tables/54full.html |title=World Cup 1954 finals |access-date=17 August 2015 |website=[[RSSSF]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306144940/http://rsssf.com/tables/54full.html |archive-date=6 March 2016}}</ref> Throughout most of their tournament matches in the 1970s, 1980s and 1990s, the team played in a [[Formation (association football)|4–4–2 formation]].<ref name="rsssf70">{{cite web |url=https://www.rsssf.org/tables/70full.html |title=World Cup 1970 finals |access-date=17 August 2015 |website=[[RSSSF]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160701154217/http://www.rsssf.com/tables/70full.html |archive-date=1 July 2016}}</ref><ref name="rsssf82">{{cite web |url=https://www.rsssf.org/tables/82full.html |title=World Cup 1982 finals |access-date=17 August 2015 |website=[[RSSSF]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160701154256/http://www.rsssf.com/tables/82full.html |archive-date=1 July 2016}}</ref><ref name="rsssf94">{{cite web |url=https://www.rsssf.org/tables/94full.html |title=World Cup 1994 finals |access-date=17 August 2015 |website=[[RSSSF]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160629194938/http://www.rsssf.com/tables/94full.html |archive-date=29 June 2016}}</ref> Since Raymond Goethals' stint in the 1970s, a key strength of the Belgian squad has been their systematic use of the [[Offside (association football)|offside trap]],<ref>{{cite news |title=Cools make it too hot for Spain |newspaper=[[The Herald (Glasgow)|The Glasgow Herald]] |date=16 June 1980 |access-date=30 June 2014 |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=2507&dat=19800614&id=ZsJAAAAAIBAJ&pg=2984,3388441}}</ref> a defensive tactic that was already intensively applied in the 1960s by Anderlecht coach [[Pierre Sinibaldi]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Sinibaldi, le Béjart mauve |trans-title=Sinibaldi, the purple Béjart |newspaper=[[La Libre Belgique|La Libre]] |first=Jean-Claude |last=Matgen |language=fr |date=27 January 2012 |access-date=9 July 2013 |url=http://www.lalibre.be/archive/sinibaldi-le-bejart-mauve-51b8e453e4b0de6db9c53280 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160701154351/http://www.lalibre.be/archive/sinibaldi-le-bejart-mauve-51b8e453e4b0de6db9c53280 |archive-date=1 July 2016}}</ref> According to football journalist Wim De Bock, "master tactician" Goethals represented the "conservative, defensive football of the Belgian national team"; he added that in the 1970s, the contrast between the Belgian playing style and the Netherlands' [[Total Football]] "could not be bigger".{{sfn|De Bock|2013}}

At the 1998 World Cup, Georges Leekens chose a [[Formation (association football)|4–3–3]] arrangement for Belgium's second and third group matches.<ref name="rsssf98">{{cite web |url=https://www.rsssf.org/tables/98full.html |title=World Cup 1998 finals |access-date=17 August 2015 |website=[[RSSSF]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160701154455/http://www.rsssf.com/tables/98full.html |archive-date=1 July 2016}}</ref> Robert Waseige said that "above all, [his] 4–4–2 system [was] holy", in the sense that he left good attackers on the bench to keep his favourite formation.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.standaard.be/cnt/dst9910050036 |title=Behoudsgezinde bondscoach Robert Waseige verandert slechts uit noodzaak |trans-title=Conservative national manager Robert Waseige only changes out of necessity |publisher=[[De Standaard]] |language=nl |first=Ludo |last=Vandewalle |date=5 October 1999 |access-date=18 August 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160701154534/http://www.standaard.be/cnt/dst9910050036 |archive-date=1 July 2016}}</ref> Wilmots opted for the 4–3–3 line-up again,<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://sportmagazine.knack.be/sport/voetbal-nationaal/marc-wilmots-wil-sommige-rode-duivels-meer-vrijheid-geven/article-normal-435091.html |title=Marc Wilmots wil sommige Rode Duivels meer vrijheid geven |trans-title=Marc Wilmots want to give some Red Devils more freedom |language=nl |journal=Sport/Voetbalmagazine |first1=Stéphane |last1=Vande Velde |first2=Pierre |last2=Bilic |date=8 October 2014 |access-date=25 August 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160629195633/http://sportmagazine.knack.be/sport/voetbal-nationaal/marc-wilmots-wil-sommige-rode-duivels-meer-vrijheid-geven/article-normal-435091.html |archive-date=29 June 2016}}</ref> with the intention of showing dominant football against any country.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://sporza.be/cm/sporza/videozone/archief/MG_sportnieuws/MG_voetbal/1.1426775 |title=Wilmots: "Dominant en intelligent proberen te spelen" |trans-title=Wilmots: "Trying to play dominantly and intelligently" |language=nl |newspaper=[[Sporza]] |date=10 September 2012 |access-date=18 August 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160629200026/http://sporza.be/cm/sporza/videozone/archief/MG_sportnieuws/MG_voetbal/1.1426775 |archive-date=29 June 2016}}</ref>

