===Notable===
[[File:PaulVanHimst1964.jpg|thumb|left|160px|[[Paul Van Himst]] in 1964 |alt=Player on the pitch in national team outfit]]
In the team's first decade, striker [[Robert De Veen]] scored 26 goals in 23 international appearances.<ref name="RSSSF BelIntRec">{{cite web|url=https://www.rsssf.org/miscellaneous/belg-recintlp.html |first=Karel |last=Stokkermans |title=Belgium – Record International Players |date=24 July 2014 |access-date=6 February 2018 |website=[[RSSSF]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180121074251/http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/belg-recintlp.html |archive-date=21 January 2018}}</ref> Richard Henshaw described [[Alphonse Six]] as "Belgium's greatest player in the prewar period&nbsp;... [who] was often called the most skillful forward outside Great Britain".{{sfn|Henshaw|1979|p=76}} The key player of the victorious 1920 Olympic squad was [[Robert Coppée]], who scored a [[hat-trick]] against Spain's [[Ricardo Zamora]],<ref name="FIFA1920">{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/archive/mensolympic/antwerp1920/matches/round=197011/match=32282/index.html |title=Olympic Football Tournament Antwerp 1920 – Belgium 3:1 (1:0) Spain – Overview |publisher=[[FIFA]] |access-date=26 August 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160630202318/http://www.fifa.com/tournaments/archive/mensolympic/antwerp1920/matches/round%3D197011/match%3D32282/index.html |archive-date=30 June 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref> and the penalty in the final.<ref name="1920finalFIFA">{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/archive/mensolympic/antwerp1920/matches/round=197018/match=32288/index.html |title=Olympic Football Tournament Antwerp 1920 – Belgium 2:0 (2:0) Czechoslovakia – Overview |publisher=[[FIFA]] |access-date=16 July 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160716194337/http://www.fifa.com/tournaments/archive/mensolympic/antwerp1920/matches/round%3D197018/match%3D32288/index.html |archive-date=16 July 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Other Belgian strikers in the interwar period were former top scorer [[Bernard Voorhoof]] and "Belgium's football grandmaster" [[Raymond Braine]],<ref name="AllRedD"/><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.delpher.nl/nl/kranten/view?coll=ddd&identifier=ddd%3A110583572%3Ampeg21%3Aa0147 |title=Raymond Braine nog steeds België's voetbalgrootmeester. |trans-title=Raymond Braine still Belgium's football grandmaster. |via=[[Delpher]] |language=nl |newspaper=[[De Telegraaf]] |date=9 October 1941 |access-date=13 June 2015}}</ref> considered "one of the greatest players of the era".{{sfn|Murray|1998|p=63}}

Other players in the 1940s and 1950s included [[Defender (association football)|centre-back]] [[Louis Carré (footballer)|Louis Carré]] and attackers [[Jef Mermans]], [[Léopold Anoul|Pol Anoul]] and [[Henri Coppens|Rik Coppens]];{{sfn|Henshaw|1979|p=76}} at the 1954 World Cup, Anoul shone with three goals,<ref name="rsssf54"/> and newspaper ''[[L'Équipe]]'' named Coppens the event's best centre forward.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/ru2pjpm2 |title=Rik Coppens |language=nl |date=29 April 2010 |access-date=19 July 2016}}</ref> The 1960s and the early 1970s were the glory days of forward and four-time [[Belgian Golden Shoe]] Paul Van Himst,<ref name="GoScho">{{cite news |url=http://sporza.be/cm/sporza/voetbal/Jupiler_Pro_League/1.1843629 |title=Van Himst en Anderlecht kapen de Gouden Schoen |trans-title=Van Himst and Anderlecht seize the Golden Shoe |language=nl |newspaper=[[Sporza]] |date=22 January 2014 |access-date=26 August 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160630202559/http://sporza.be/cm/sporza/voetbal/Jupiler_Pro_League/1.1843629 |archive-date=30 June 2016}}</ref> later elected Belgian [[UEFA Jubilee Awards|UEFA Golden Player]] of 1954–2003 and Belgium's Player of the Century by [[International Federation of Football History & Statistics|IFFHS]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Belgium still bows to Van Himst |publisher=[[UEFA]] |first=Berend |last=Scholten |date=21 January 2011 |access-date=3 May 2014 |url=https://www.uefa.com/news-media/news/01ed-0f863170124b-3f237ca970f6-1000--belgium-still-bows-to-van-himst/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151107172446/http://www.uefa.com/memberassociations/association%3Dbel/news/newsid%3D140820.html |archive-date=7 November 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rsssf.org/miscellaneous/iffhs-country-complete.html |title=IFFHS' Players and Keepers of the Century for many countries |first=Marcelo |last=Leme de Arruda |date=21 January 2000 |access-date=14 May 2015 |website=[[RSSSF]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160630202741/http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/iffhs-country-complete.html |archive-date=30 June 2016}}</ref> [[File:Eden Hazard 2018.jpg|thumb|[[Eden Hazard]], former team [[captain (association football)|captain]] and third top scoring player for Belgium<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44748604|title=World Cup 2018: England finish fourth after Belgium defeat|access-date=14 July 2018|work=BBC Sport}}</ref>|alt=|252x252px]] At the [[1965 Ballon d'Or]], Van Himst ranked fourth, achieving Belgium's highest ever position at the European football election.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rsssf.org/miscellaneous/europa-poy65.html |title=European Footballer of the Year ("Ballon d'Or") 1965 |first=José Luis |last=Pierrend |date=22 June 2005 |access-date=16 July 2016 |website=[[RSSSF]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160716194423/http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/europa-poy65.html |archive-date=16 July 2016}}</ref> Decades after Coppens and Van Himst had retired from playing football, a journalist on a Flemish television show asked them "Who [from both of you] was the best, actually?". Coppens replied: "I will ask Paul that&nbsp;... If Paul says it was me, then he's right".<ref>{{cite news |url=http://sporza.be/cm/sporza/videozone/retro/Retro_Rik_Coppens/1.2230978 |language=nl |title=Coppens: 'Als Paul zegt dat ik het was, dan heeft hij gelijk' |trans-title=Coppens: 'If Paul says it was me, then he is right' |newspaper=[[Sporza]] |date=6 February 2015 |access-date=11 August 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150206232313/http://sporza.be/cm/sporza/videozone/retro/Retro_Rik_Coppens/1.2230978 |archive-date=6 February 2015}}</ref> In 1966, striker [[Raoul Lambert]] and defending midfielder [[Wilfried Van Moer]] joined the national team;<ref name="AllRedD" /> while the UEFA praised Lambert for his skills at Euro 1972,<ref>{{cite web|title=1972 team of the tournament |url=https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/news/0253-0d7bd0da58f2-d557c23f55fa-1000--euro-1972-team-of-the-tournament/ |publisher=[[UEFA]] |date=2 May 2011 |access-date=23 January 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160630202927/http://www.uefa.com/news/newsid%3D1621340.html |archive-date=30 June 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref> Van Moer won three Golden Shoes and equalled Van Himst's fourth rank at the [[1980 Ballon d'Or]].<ref name="GoScho" /><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rsssf.org/miscellaneous/europa-poy80.html |title=European Footballer of the Year ("Ballon d'Or") 1980 |first=José Luis |last=Pierrend |date=1 May 2005 |access-date=16 July 2016 |website=[[RSSSF]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160716194511/http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/europa-poy80.html |archive-date=16 July 2016}}</ref>

Belgium has seen two talented waves since 1980, from which several players in defensive positions gained international fame. In the 1980s and the early 1990s, goalkeepers [[Jean-Marie Pfaff]] and [[Michel Preud'homme]] were elected best [[Glossary of association football terms#C|custodian]]s at the FIFA World Cup,<ref name="AllStar"/><ref name="FIFAWCAwards">{{cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/mm/document/fifafacts/mcwc/ip-301_03a_fwc-awards_22643.pdf |title=FIFA World Cups: Awards |publisher=[[FIFA]] |access-date=19 June 2007 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160630203029/http://www.fifa.com/mm/document/fifafacts/mcwc/ip-301_03a_fwc-awards_22643.pdf |archive-date=30 June 2016}}</ref> while FIFA recognised midfielders [[Jan Ceulemans]] and [[Enzo Scifo]] as the propelling forces of Belgium's 1986 World Cup squad.<ref name="AllStar">{{cite web |url=http://football.sporting99.com/fifa-world-cup-all-star-team.html |title=FIFA World Cup All-Star Team – Football world Cup All Star Team |website=Football.sporting99.com |access-date=28 June 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160630203237/http://football.sporting99.com/fifa-world-cup-all-star-team.html |archive-date=30 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/fifa-tournaments/players-coaches/people=44619/profile.html |title=FIFA Classic Player: Scifo, a Red Devil with divine gifts |publisher=[[FIFA]] |access-date=2 May 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160630203359/http://www.fifa.com/fifa-tournaments/players-coaches/people%3D44619/profile.html |archive-date=30 June 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref> In 2002, after all players of this generation had retired,<ref name="AllRedD"/> Marc Wilmots became Belgium's top scorer at the World Cup with five goals.<ref name="rsssf2002" /><ref name="rsssf98"/>

During the 10 years from 2002 to 2012 in which Belgium failed to qualify for a major tournament, another [[Golden generation#Belgium (2014–2022)|golden generation]] emerged, many of whom gained both prime individual and team awards in top European clubs and competitions.{{efn|Prime individual awards include being elected the season's or year's best player of a competition; prime team awards equal winning a competition. National top divisions, main national cup competitions, [[UEFA Champions League]] and [[UEFA Europa League]] are considered.}} These include defender [[Vincent Kompany]],<ref>{{cite news |title=Alan Pardew and Vincent Kompany's Premier League award |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/18042404 |publisher=[[BBC Sport]] |date=11 May 2012 |access-date=16 January 2014}}</ref><ref name="SoccerwayKompany">{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/vincent-kompany/1998/ |title=Belgium – V. Kompany |publisher=Soccerway |access-date=16 July 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130206171311/http://int.soccerway.com/players/vincent-kompany/1998/ |archive-date=6 February 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref> midfielder [[Kevin De Bruyne]], one of the best attacking midfielders in the world and his generation;<ref name="SporzaDeBruyne">{{cite news |url=http://sporza.be/cm/sporza/voetbal/buitenland/Duitsland/1.2400701 |title=De Bruyne is Speler van het Jaar volgens Duitse Journalisten |trans-title=De Bruyne is Player of the Year according to German journalists |language=nl |date=26 July 2015 |access-date=26 July 2015 |newspaper=[[Sporza]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160716195857/http://sporza.be/cm/sporza/voetbal/buitenland/Duitsland/1.2400701 |archive-date=16 July 2016}}</ref> and winger [[Eden Hazard]], who has been praised as one of [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]]'s greatest-ever players<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/world-cup/2018/06/26/eden-hazard-can-best-chelsea-player-history/ |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220111/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/world-cup/2018/06/26/eden-hazard-can-best-chelsea-player-history/ |archive-date=11 January 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live|website=The Telegraph|title= Eden Hazard can be the best Chelsea player in history|date=26 June 2018|access-date=18 November 2019}}{{cbignore}}</ref> and one of his era's best footballers in the world.<ref>{{cite news|url= https://talksport.com/football/426952/eden-hazard-best-in-the-world-chelsea-legend-john-terry/ |website=Talk Sport|title=  BETTER THAN MESSI Eden Hazard is the best player in the WORLD, claims Chelsea legend John Terry|date=5 August 2018|access-date=20 November 2019}}</ref> Hazard is ranked third after [[Romelu Lukaku]] and [[Kevin De Bruyne]] on Belgium's all-time scoring leaderboard.<ref name="PLEHazard">{{cite web |url=http://www.premierleague.com/en-gb/news/news/2014-15/may/220515-mourinho-and-hazard-claim-barclays-season-awards-for-2015.html |title=Mourinho and Hazard scoop Barclays season awards |publisher=[[Premier League]] |date=22 May 2015 |access-date=26 May 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150526022459/http://www.premierleague.com/en-gb/news/news/2014-15/may/220515-mourinho-and-hazard-claim-barclays-season-awards-for-2015.html |archive-date=26 May 2015}}</ref><ref name="SoccerwayEHazard">{{cite web |url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/eden-hazard/39358/ |title=Belgium – E. Hazard |publisher=Soccerway |access-date=16 July 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160716195811/http://int.soccerway.com/players/eden-hazard/39358/ |archive-date=16 July 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Honourable mentions of this golden generation are [[Thibaut Courtois]], [[Jan Vertonghen]], [[Dries Mertens]], and [[Toby Alderweireld]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/cybrown/2018/07/11/the-2018-world-cup-was-belgiums-golden-generations-best-but-not-last-shot-at-a-major-trophy/#4c3e9de47c9a|website=Forbes|title=For Belgium's 'Golden Generation,' 2018 World Cup Was Best (But Not Last) Shot At A Major Trophy|date=11 July 2018|access-date=18 November 2019}}</ref> These players helped Belgium finish at the third place at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]], the team's best result at the tournament, and reach No. 1 on FIFA's rankings twice, since 2015.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44748604|title=World Cup 2018: England finish fourth after Belgium defeat|date=14 July 2018|work=BBC Sport|access-date=16 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|url=https://www.fifa.com/fifa-world-ranking/men|title=Men's Ranking|date=24 October 2019|work=FIFA|access-date=18 November 2019}}</ref>

