===UEFA European Championship===
{{Update section|date=May 2025}}
{{Main|Belgium at the UEFA European Championship}}
[[File:BEL-FRG 1980-06-22.svg|thumb|220px|Line-ups of the [[UEFA Euro 1980 final|Euro 1980 final]]: Belgium (red) against West Germany|alt=Scheme of football pitch with the line-ups of a red team in 4-4-2 formation against a white team in 5-3-2 formation]]
Belgium have qualified for the [[UEFA European Championship]] seven times, and has hosted or co-hosted the event twice; they were chosen to accommodate [[UEFA Euro 1972|1972]]{{efn|The other bids were from England and Italy,<ref>{{cite news |title=Sportflitsen |trans-title=Sports flashes |url=http://www.delpher.nl/nl/kranten/view?coll=ddd&identifier=ddd%3A011236337%3Ampeg21%3Aa0119 |newspaper=[[De Tijd (Netherlands)|De Tijd]] |via=[[Delpher]] |language=nl |date=14 March 1972 |access-date=19 September 2015 }}</ref><ref name="rsssf72"/>}} and [[UEFA Euro 2000|2000]], co-hosting the latter with the Netherlands.<ref name="rsssf2000">{{cite web |url=https://www.rsssf.org/tables/00e.html |title=European Championship 2000 |first1=John |last1=Beuker |first2=Karel |last2=Stokkermans |date=17 January 2004 |access-date=27 August 2015 |website=[[RSSSF]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160701150016/http://www.rsssf.com/tables/00e.html |archive-date=1 July 2016}}</ref>

At Euro 1972, Belgium finished third after losing 1–2 against West Germany and beating Hungary 2–1.<ref name="rsssf72">{{cite web |url=https://www.rsssf.org/tables/72e.html |title=European Championship 1972 |first1=Karel |last1=Stokkermans |first2=Martín |last2=Tabeira |date=31 January 2007 |access-date=10 November 2014 |website=[[RSSSF]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160701150050/http://www.rsssf.com/tables/72e.html |archive-date=1 July 2016}}</ref> The team's best continental result is runners-up at [[UEFA Euro 1980|Euro 1980]] in Italy, losing to West Germany. 
West Germany's [[Horst Hrubesch]] scored first, but [[René Vandereycken]] equalised courtesy of a penalty. Two minutes before the regular playing time ended, Hrubesch scored again denying Belgium a first European title.<ref name="rsssf80">{{cite web |url=https://www.rsssf.org/tables/80e.html |title=European Championship 1980 |first1=Karel |last1=Stokkermans |first2=Martín |last2=Tabeira |date=28 March 2007 |access-date=27 August 2015 |website=[[RSSSF]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160701150124/http://www.rsssf.com/tables/80e.html |archive-date=1 July 2016}}</ref>

At Euro 1984, in their last and decisive group match against [[Denmark national football team|Denmark]], the Belgian team took a 0–2 lead, but the Danes won the match 3–2.<ref name="rsssf84det">{{cite web|url=https://www.rsssf.org/tables/84e-full.html |title=European Championship 1984 – Final Tournament – Full Details |first=Barrie |last=Courtney |date=19 June 2004 |access-date=27 August 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20011126124457/http://www.rsssf.com/tables/84e-full.html |archive-date=26 November 2001 |website=[[RSSSF]] |url-status=live }}</ref> Sixteen years later, Belgium reappeared at the Euros as co-hosts, qualifying automatically, but the Belgians were eliminated in the group stage.<ref name="rsssf2000"/>

Belgium exited in the quarter-finals of [[UEFA Euro 2016]], losing to Wales.<ref name="EC2016Wal">{{cite web |url=http://www.espnfc.com/match?gameId=438159 |title=Wales stun Belgium to reach Euro semifinal |publisher=[[ESPN FC]] |date=1 July 2016 |access-date=2 July 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160721111357/http://www.espnfc.com/match?gameId=438159 |archive-date=21 July 2016}}</ref>
