===Olympic Games===
{{Main|Belgium at the Olympics}}
[[File:BEL-LUX SO1928.JPG|thumb|upright=1.2|Hectic phase during the goal-rich Olympic win against [[Luxembourg national football team|Luxembourg]] in 1928 (5–3)|alt=Aerial play with two Belgian players and the Luxembourg keeper trying to touch the ball]]
The football tournament for senior men's national teams took place in six Summer Olympics between 1908 and 1936. The Belgian squad participated in all three [[Football at the Summer Olympics|Olympic Games]] in the 1920s and won the gold medal at home at the 1920 edition.<ref name="results"/><ref name="rsssfOG20">{{cite web |url=https://www.rsssf.org/tableso/ol1920f.html |title=Games of the VIII. Olympiad – Football Tournament |first1=Karel |last1=Stokkermans |first2=Mikael |last2=Jönsson |date=26 June 2008 |access-date=27 August 2015 |website=[[RSSSF]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160701150243/http://www.rsssf.com/tableso/ol1920f.html |archive-date=1 July 2016}}</ref> Two other Belgian delegations appeared at the Olympics. At the [[Football at the 1900 Summer Olympics|1900 Summer Olympics]], [[Football at the 1900 Summer Olympics – Men's team squads#Université de Bruxelles|a Belgian representation]] with mainly students won bronze,<ref name="rsssfOG00">{{cite web |url=https://www.rsssf.org/tableso/ol1900f.html |title=Games of the II. Olympiad – Football Tournament |first1=Søren |last1=Elbech |first2=Karel |last2=Stokkermans |date=21 July 2011 |access-date=27 August 2015 |website=[[RSSSF]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160701150404/http://www.rsssf.com/tableso/ol1900f.html |archive-date=1 July 2016}}</ref> and at [[Football at the 2008 Summer Olympics|the 2008 edition]], Belgium's U-23 selection placed fourth.<ref name="rsssfOG2008">{{cite web |url=https://www.rsssf.org/tableso/ol2008f.html |title=Games of the XXIX. Olympiad – Football Tournament |first=Karel |last=Stokkermans |date=14 March 2013 |access-date=27 August 2015 |website=[[RSSSF]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160701150434/http://www.rsssf.com/tableso/ol2008f.html |archive-date=1 July 2016}}</ref>

[[Football at the 1920 Summer Olympics – Men's team squads# Belgium|Belgium's 1920 Olympic squad]] was given a [[bye (sports)|bye]] into the quarter-finals, where they won 3–1 against Spain, and reached the semi-finals, where they beat the Netherlands 3–0. In the first half of the final against Czechoslovakia, the Belgians led 2–0.<ref name="rsssfOG20"/> Forward Robert Coppée converted a disputed early [[penalty kick (association football)|penalty]], and the action in which attacker [[Henri Larnoe]] doubled the score was also a matter of debate.<ref name="ISOH"/><ref name="FIFA1920"/> After the [[Fouls and misconduct (association football)|dismissal]] of the Czechoslovak left-back Karel Steiner, the discontented visitors left the pitch in the 40th minute. Afterwards, the away team reported their reasons for protest to the Olympic organisation;<ref name="ISOH">{{cite journal |first=Juan |last=Fauria í García |date=1993 |title=The 1920 Football (Soccer) Tournament |url=https://library.la84.org/SportsLibrary/JOH/JOHv1n4/JOHv1n4d.pdf#search='1920%20Czechoslovakia%20football' |journal=ISOH Magazine |volume=1 |issue=4 |pages=5–7 |access-date=4 May 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131228140336/http://library.la84.org/SportsLibrary/JOH/JOHv1n4/JOHv1n4d.pdf |archive-date=28 December 2013}}</ref> these complaints were dismissed and the Czechoslovaks were disqualified.{{sfn|Henshaw|1979|p=76}} The 2–0 score was allowed to stand and Belgium were crowned the champions.{{sfn|Henshaw|1979|p=76}}
